## Minimal fog-docker settings for a portable laptop server
##
## See fog-docker docs:
## https://88fingerslukee.github.io/fog-docker/
##
## FOG version: pin the container image to a fog-docker release tag so you run a
## known upstream FOG Project build (not an arbitrary moving :latest).
## Current default in docker-compose.yml matches the latest fog-docker release
## at the time this repo was updated; check for newer tags:
##   https://github.com/88fingerslukee/fog-docker/releases
FOG_DOCKER_IMAGE=ghcr.io/88fingerslukee/fog-docker:fog-1.5.10.1826

# The IP/FQDN clients use to reach the web UI (imaging network IP is typical)
FOG_WEB_HOST=10.0.0.5

# Database root password (choose your own)
FOG_DB_ROOT_PASSWORD=changeme

# Optional: timezone
TZ=UTC

